      <p>"We actually got several Hindenburg omens firing this week," Kranzle notes. "That speaks to a bifurcated market where some sectors are really hurting while others are thriving."</p>

      <p><strong class="text-white">Semiconductor parabola (SMH up 41% in weeks):</strong> The semiconductor ETF has moved 41% in just a few weeks. This is not normal. This is the kind of vertical move that historically precedes sharp reversals.</p>

